abstract: Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.
snippet: Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the Whi...
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.
headline_main: Rivals Question Front-Runner Sanders' Electability at Rowdy South Carolina Democratic Debate
headline_print_headline: Rivals Question Front-Runner Sanders' Electability at Rowdy South Carolina Democratic Debate

abstract: Tonight’s debate could also be a critical test for Michael Bloomberg. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: Tonight’s debate could also be a critical test for Michael Bloomberg. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., was rushed out of an appearance at a McDonald’s workers’ strike by protesters in Charleston, S.C., on Monday. The workers were calling for a $15 per hour minimum wage. The protesters chanted, “Pete can’t be our president! Where was 15 in South Bend!”

headline_main: Divisiveness Among 2020 Democratic Hopefuls Hits New Level
headline_print_headline: A Sign of the Times? The Democratic Primary Has Become a Free-for-All

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates face off before the South Carolina primary, and Pete Davidson debuts his first Netflix comedy special.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates face off before the South Carolina primary, and Pete Davidson debuts his first Netflix comedy special.
lead_paragraph: DEMOCRATIC PRESIDENTIAL DEBATE 8 p.m. on CBS. Seven candidates have qualified for this debate in Charleston, S.C.: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York, former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota; and the billionaire businessman Tom Steyer. A lot is riding on their performances. The debate comes four days before the South Carolina primary and just before the Super Tuesday primaries and caucuses on March 3. Bloomberg may try to redeem himself after scathing attacks on the debate in Las Vegas last week. Warren came out strong with an aggressive performance, while Sanders walked away mostly unharmed, politics reporters for The New York Times wrote in an analysis.

abstract: South Carolina state Sen. Gerald Malloy is fine with a gay presidential candidate like Pete Buttigieg. His older male relatives are not — and that may be the defining challenge of Buttigieg's campaign.
snippet: South Carolina state Sen. Gerald Malloy is fine with a gay presidential candidate like Pete Buttigieg. His older male relatives are not — and that may be the defining challenge of Buttigieg's campaign.
lead_paragraph: CONWAY, S.C. — South Carolina state Sen. Gerald Malloy is fine with a gay presidential candidate like Pete Buttigieg. His older male relatives are not — and that may be the defining challenge of Buttigieg's campaign.
headline_main: In SC, Buttigieg Faces Black Voters Wary of a Gay Candidate
headline_print_headline: In SC, Buttigieg Faces Black Voters Wary of a Gay Candidate

abstract: After months of resistance to discussing how he would pay for his plans like “Medicare for all” and canceling student debt, Mr. Sanders announced the explanation at a CNN event on Monday.
snippet: After months of resistance to discussing how he would pay for his plans like “Medicare for all” and canceling student debt, Mr. Sanders announced the explanation at a CNN event on Monday.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, under growing pressure to explain how he would pay for his very expensive policy agenda, released a checklist on Monday evening that he described as a full explanation of how he would finance all of his proposals.
